==Image albums==
In 2005, three CDs were promoted as "image albums", each one with seven tracks: one [[opening]] with vocals, three instrumental intervals, one dedicated to each person, one ending with vocals and the opening and ending songs of the series in [[karaoke]] format. Each image album was assigned to one of the three families of roses; the songs were sung by the voice actors of the anime series. The first and fifth tracks are sung by the voice actors; the second, third, and fourth tracks are instrumentals, and the last two tracks are karaoke versions.

